Create A Medical Image Annotation Job

Instructions

Overview

Help us determine if there are any signs of pneumonia in the provided X-ray images by analyzing key indicators such as lung opacity and diaphragm shadows. Your input will assist in accurately classifying the presence or absence of pneumonia for medical diagnosis.

Steps

  1. Examine the X-ray image carefully.
  2. If signs of pneumonia are present, select the corresponding option.
  3. If you observe any symptoms not listed, type the name of the symptom into the provided text box.
  4. Use the plus icon next to the text box to add additional symptoms.
  5. Ensure that each symptom is entered on a separate line.

Rules Tips

Rules:

  • Only check for signs of pneumonia or relevant symptoms in the X-ray image.
  • If multiple instances of the same symptom are observed, you only need to list it once.

Tips:

  • If the X-ray image is unclear or has multiple views, make sure to examine all parts of the image thoroughly before making your assessment.
